arXiv:2503.05865v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We analyze publicly available $K^+ 	o \pi^+ 
u  ar{
u}$ data collected by NA62 from 2016 to 2022 to constrain the vectorial axion-down-strange coupling or, equivalently, the Peccei-Quinn scale $f_a$ rescaled by this coupling, obtaining $|(F_V)_{23}| > 1.1 	imes 10^{12}$ GeV. Under the complementary assumption that axion production is dominated by weak amplitudes, we derive a model-independent bound on $f_a$, namely $f_a > 1.0 	imes 10^5$ GeV. We also discuss the potential of applying the same approach to $K^+ 	o \pi^+ \pi^0 
u  ar{
u}$ data, from which we estimate the bound $|(F_A)_{23}| > 1.0 	imes 10^8$ GeV. These constraints represent the strongest existing bounds inferred from controlled experimental setups.
